.\" Simple Roff Document Example
.\" This is a comment line
.TH SAMPLE 1 "February 2026" "Version 1.0" "User Manual"
.SH NAME
sample \- a simple roff document example
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sample
[\fB\-h\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR]
[\fIfile\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
This is a simple roff document that demonstrates basic formatting capabilities.
Roff is a powerful text formatting system used primarily for creating
.B man pages
and technical documentation.
.PP
This paragraph shows how to create multiple paragraphs using the
.B .PP
macro. Roff processes text line by line and applies formatting macros.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Display help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-v
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.I file
Specify the input file to process.
.SH EXAMPLES
Here are some usage examples:
.PP
.nf
    sample input.txt
    sample \-h
    sample \-v
.fi
.SH FORMATTING EXAMPLES
.SS Text Styles
This demonstrates
.B bold text,
.I italic text,
and
.BR "bold italic" .
.SS Lists
You can create lists like this:
.IP \(bu 3
First item in the list
.IP \(bu 3
Second item in the list
.IP \(bu 3
Third item in the list
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR groff (1),
.BR man (1),
.BR troff (1)
